computation_methods:
MVA proportion to GDP is calculated by dividing MVA by GDP of the whole country.
MVA share с =GVAс/GDP*100 
where, 
MVA share с –  Manufacturing value added share in GDP; 
MVAс – manufacturing value added; 
GDP – gross domestic product.
MVA per capita is the ratio of total gross manufacturing value added over a period of time to the de-facto population.
MVAcPC=MVAc/P 
where, 
MVAcPC – manufacturing value added per capita; 
MVAc– manufacturing value added; 
P – de-facto population.
